We are building a floating character HUD for a Foundry VTT v14 module for the Vagabond RPG system.

## Context

The module already has a working full character sheet and uses SCSS compiled via `npm run watch`.
The HUD is a new draggable floating overlay for use during play.

Attach and read before starting:
- vagabond-character-hud-spec.md  ← full design spec
- vagabond-hud.hbs                ← reference HBS (study only, do not copy)
- vagabond-hud.css                ← reference CSS (study only, do not copy)

The reference files show the intended layout, dimensions, and design intent. They are NOT the
implementation files. You will write your own HBS and SCSS following the module's existing
patterns and naming conventions.

## Before writing any code, do the following:

1. Read all three attached files completely.

2. Search the module source for:
   - Existing ApplicationV2 class structure, naming conventions, and how apps are registered
   - The SCSS file structure and naming conventions (class prefixes used to avoid conflicts)
   - How `npm run watch` compiles SCSS — confirm the entry point and output path
   - How the Spell Cast Dialog is opened — the HUD spells panel must be able to trigger it
   - Any existing drag/drop or floating window patterns already in use

3. Search the Vagabond system source (`systems/vagabond/`) for:
   - Every data field path listed in spec section 12 — confirm each one
   - The existing Hindered/Favored toggle — find its `data-action` and reuse it exactly
   - How the system rolls saves — exact method signature
   - How the system rolls skills — exact method signature  
   - How weapon attacks are rolled — exact method signature
   - How spells are cast — exact method signature (connects to Spell Cast Dialog)
   - FA icon classes used for HP, Fatigue, Speed, Luck, and the three saves — find them in
     the system's HBS templates, do not assume
   - Where the character sheet persists hotbar/slot assignments (actor flags or system field)
   - Whether the system has any existing compact HUD we should be aware of

4. Search the Foundry V14 API for:
   - How to make an ApplicationV2 draggable and persist its position per user
   - The correct hook to re-render the HUD when actor data changes
   - The DragDrop API for accepting item drops onto slots

5. Produce a planning document before writing any code. It must include:
   - File list: every new file and every existing file to modify
   - SCSS class naming strategy (prefix or namespace to avoid conflicts)
   - ApplicationV2 class structure (name, mixins, options, lifecycle methods)
   - HBS template outline (structure only, not full code)
   - Data flow: how actor data enters the HUD and stays reactive
   - Drag position persistence strategy
   - All system API calls with exact signatures from source
   - All Foundry hooks with exact names from V14 API
   - Open questions before implementation can proceed

6. Present the plan and wait for approval before writing any code.

## Constraints

- Foundry VTT v14
- ApplicationV2 + HandlebarsApplicationMixin
- SCSS via existing `npm run watch` pipeline — no new build config
- No jQuery, no external CDN dependencies at runtime
- Class names must be namespaced to avoid conflicts with the Vagabond system and other modules
- FA Pro icons: verify all class names from system source before using
- The reference HBS and CSS are for inspiration only — write fresh files in module structure
- "Click = roll" everywhere: no confirmation dialogs except the Spell Cast Dialog
- HUD floats freely — player drags it, position persists per user in Foundry flags
- Panel (tab content) opens above or below HUD depending on available screen space
- Nothing writes to actor/item until an action is explicitly confirmed
